The paper deals with biometric identification and template protection, which are closely related to computer security (cs.CR). The proposed scheme involves image processing and Fourier domain representation, which are common in computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. The use of low-rank approximation and minimum spanning tree also suggests a possible connection to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
